INSERT INTO `core_financefact` VALUES (1,'The Dollar Index, which measures the strength of the US dollar against a basket of foreign currencies, was set at 100 when it was created in 1973. It has fluctuated significantly since then, reflecting changing global economic conditions.','General',1,'2025-03-14 18:01:44.132826'),(2,'Most money today exists only digitally. Physical currency (coins and banknotes) represents less than 10% of the total money supply in most developed economies, with the rest existing as electronic records in banking systems.','General',1,'2025-03-14 18:01:56.548433'),(3,'Modern portfolio theory, developed by Harry Markowitz in 1952, demonstrated mathematically that diversification across uncorrelated assets can reduce risk without sacrificing returns. This groundbreaking work earned Markowitz a Nobel Prize in Economics in 1990.','General',1,'2025-03-14 19:28:42.050733'),(4,'The \"January Effect\" is a calendar anomaly where stock prices historically tend to rise more in January than in other months. This phenomenon is attributed to tax-loss harvesting in December and new investment allocations at the beginning of the year.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:07:37.077421'),(5,'The term \"hedge fund\" originated from the practice of \"hedging\" investments against market downturns. The first hedge fund was created by Alfred Winslow Jones in 1949, who combined long positions in undervalued stocks with short positions in overvalued ones.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:07:45.914382'),(6,'The term \"hedge fund\" originated from the practice of \"hedging\" investments against market downturns. The first hedge fund was created by Alfred Winslow Jones in 1949, who combined long positions in undervalued stocks with short positions in overvalued ones.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:07:54.799200'),(7,'Approximately 80% of day traders lose money in their first year of trading, with only about 1% consistently profitable over the long term according to various academic studies.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:08:08.304568'),(8,'Credit scores were first introduced in 1989 by FICO (Fair Isaac Corporation). Before this standardized system, lenders would make subjective decisions based on personal relationships and reputation rather than data-driven metrics.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:08:17.709393'),(9,'The concept of compound interest, often called the \"eighth wonder of the world,\" can turn small investments into substantial wealth over time. For example, $10,000 invested with an 8% annual return would grow to over $100,000 in 30 years without adding a penny more.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:08:25.262939'),(10,'Behavioral finance research shows that investors typically feel the pain of losses about twice as intensely as they feel the pleasure of equivalent gains, a phenomenon known as \"loss aversion.\" This psychological bias often leads to poor investment decisions.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:08:39.484249'),(11,'The New York Stock Exchange was founded in 1792 under a buttonwood tree on Wall Street when 24 brokers signed the Buttonwood Agreement. Today, it lists companies with a combined market capitalization exceeding $30 trillion.','General',1,'2025-05-17 12:08:47.098369');
